Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper discusses the use of deep linguistic processing technology to create challenging abstract datasets for language understanding tasks, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper also discusses visual question answering, which is a task related to computer vision and falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper discusses the use of artificial data to address problems with standard approaches to evaluation, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the evaluation of multimodal deep learning models, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper discusses the use of deep linguistic processing technology to create datasets, which can be relevant to information retrieval tasks such as text classification and information extraction.
